  "text": "Since X is a simplicial toric variety, its rational Chow ring A * (X ) Q has an explicit presentation; see [CITATION_1] §5.2] . Specifically, if D j is the torus-invariant Weil divisor associated to the ray ρ j for all −m j n, then we have Choosing a shelling for the fan Σ yields a distinguished basis for A * (X ) Q ; again see [CITATION_2] §5.2] . With this in mind, we order the maximal cones of Σ by σ i, j > σ k,ℓ if i + j > k + ℓ or i + j = k + ℓ and j > ℓ. Let τ i, j be the subcone of σ i, j obtained by intersecting the maximal cone σ i, j with all cones σ k,ℓ satisfying σ k,ℓ > σ i, j and dim σ i, j ∩ σ k,ℓ = m + n − 2. We obtain a shelling for Σ (i.e. condition ( * ) in [CITATION_3] p. 101 ] is satisfied) because dim σ i, j ∩ σ k,ℓ = m + n − 2 if and only if i = k and j = ℓ or i = k and j = ℓ, so",
